{
    "name": "Tsabagu",
    "type": "alien",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Tsabagu oni come into being when a malicious spirit successfully incarnates into a shobhad. In their natural form, they\u2019re four-armed humanoids with blue skin and a dramatic brow ridge over their one baleful eye. Their powerful jaws are decorated by a pair of black tusks.<br/><br/> Shobhad culture greatly idolizes strength, and so tsabagus often quickly rise to positions of leadership or great influence. These exalted oni often set about raiding surrounding settlements to recruit more shobhads into their ever-growing fighting forces. The only authority tsabagus are willing to defer to is that of even stronger oni.<br/><br/> While tsabagus with power and influence are undoubtedly terrors on Akiton, those that make it off-world can become threats to entire systems. These tsabagus can end up leading ruthless mercenary companies or space pirate crews. Their lust for violence and domination is never satisfied, and attacks from such gangs rarely leave any survivors."
        }
    ],
